# Plan: Add PixelArt Provider Package to Vercel AI SDK

## Context

The Vercel AI SDK is a monorepo supporting many AI providers via a consistent adapter pattern. A new fictional "PixelArt" provider needs to be added that **only** supports image generation. This plan follows the exact same conventions as other providers (especially `packages/togetherai` as the closest simple reference) to ensure the package compiles cleanly and integrates properly.

---

## Files to Create

All files live under `packages/pixelart/`. No existing files are modified (except noting root `tsconfig.json` would need `{ "path": "packages/pixelart" }` added for full monorepo type-checking, but `pnpm type-check` from within the package works without it).

---

## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1 — `packages/pixelart/package.json`

Mirrors `packages/togetherai/package.json` but:
- Name: `@ai-sdk/pixelart`
- Version: `0.0.0` (new package per contributing guide)
- Remove `@ai-sdk/openai-compatible` dependency (not needed — no chat/embedding)
- Remove `prepack`/`postpack` scripts (no docs MDX exists yet)
- Keep `@ai-sdk/provider` and `@ai-sdk/provider-utils` as workspace dependencies

```json
{
  "name": "@ai-sdk/pixelart",
  "version": "0.0.0",
  "license": "Apache-2.0",
  "sideEffects": false,
  "main": "./dist/index.js",
  "module": "./dist/index.mjs",
  "types": "./dist/index.d.ts",
  "files": [
    "dist/**/*",
    "src",
    "!src/**/*.test.ts",
    "!src/**/*.test-d.ts",
    "!src/**/__snapshots__",
    "!src/**/__fixtures__",
    "CHANGELOG.md",
    "README.md"
  ],
  "scripts": {
    "build": "pnpm clean && tsup --tsconfig tsconfig.build.json",
    "build:watch": "pnpm clean && tsup --watch",
    "clean": "del-cli dist *.tsbuildinfo",
    "type-check": "tsc --build",
    "test": "pnpm test:node && pnpm test:edge",
    "test:update": "pnpm test:node -u",
    "test:watch": "vitest --config vitest.node.config.js",
    "test:edge": "vitest --config vitest.edge.config.js --run",
    "test:node": "vitest --config vitest.node.config.js --run"
  },
  "exports": {
    "./package.json": "./package.json",
    ".": {
      "types": "./dist/index.d.ts",
      "import": "./dist/index.mjs",
      "require": "./dist/index.js"
    }
  },
  "dependencies": {
    "@ai-sdk/provider": "workspace:*",
    "@ai-sdk/provider-utils": "workspace:*"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "@types/node": "20.17.24",
    "@vercel/ai-tsconfig": "workspace:*",
    "tsup": "^8",
    "typescript": "5.8.3",
    "zod": "3.25.76"
  },
  "peerDependencies": {
    "zod": "^3.25.76 || ^4.1.8"
  },
  "engines": { "node": ">=18" },
  "publishConfig": { "access": "public" },
  "homepage": "https://ai-sdk.dev/docs",
  "repository": { "type": "git", "url": "git+https://github.com/vercel/ai.git" },
  "bugs": { "url": "https://github.com/vercel/ai/issues" },
  "keywords": ["ai"]
}
```

---

### Step 2 — `packages/pixelart/tsconfig.json`

```json
{
  "extends": "./node_modules/@vercel/ai-tsconfig/ts-library.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "composite": true,
    "rootDir": "src",
    "outDir": "dist"
  },
  "exclude": ["dist", "build", "node_modules", "tsup.config.ts"],
  "references": [
    { "path": "../provider" },
    { "path": "../provider-utils" }
  ]
}
```

---

### Step 3 — `packages/pixelart/tsconfig.build.json`

```json
{
  "extends": "./tsconfig.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "composite": false
  }
}
```

---

### Step 4 — `packages/pixelart/tsup.config.ts`

Standard single-entry tsup config that injects the package version at build time:

```typescript
import { defineConfig } from 'tsup';

export default defineConfig([
  {
    entry: ['src/index.ts'],
